{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"An image containing explicit content is flagged and held for review, not published.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is model judgment quality: whether explicit imagery is actually detected. A stubbed/mocked classifier would always return the expected label and hide real misclassification failure. No multi-agent sequence is required beyond a single model decision plus downstream hold action.","test_description":"Submit a curated explicit-image evaluation set through the real vision model path and assert each item is held-for-review and never reaches publish. Include at least one known-hard edge case (cropped/low-light) to catch real model misses.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.78,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"A text post containing hate speech is flagged regardless of obfuscation techniques (e.g., letter substitution, unicode lookalikes).","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This behavior explicitly targets robustness of model output under adversarial text transformations. Deterministic mocks cannot reveal failures in actual hate-speech detection quality on obfuscated inputs.","test_description":"Run a real text-model moderation suite with hate-speech samples transformed via leetspeak, homoglyphs, spacing, and punctuation obfuscation; assert flagged=true and held-for-review for each variant.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.84,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A post that passes both content checks is published rather than held or silently dropped.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Primary failure is orchestration/state handoff between moderation modules and publish module (pass+pass => publish). This can be caught with deterministic pass outputs from both classifiers; correctness does not require validating model judgment quality. Rejected higher level (Agentic): behavior text conditions on already-passed checks, not on whether models made semantically correct classifications.","test_description":"Wire moderation service + decision engine + persistence/queue in-process. Stub image/text classifiers to return PASS, submit a post, assert exactly one published record/event and zero hold/drop outcomes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.09,"Integration":0.71,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The full moderation pipeline — image check, text check, publish decision — completes within 5 seconds of submission.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is end-to-end latency across multiple agentic steps in sequence (vision decision, text decision, final decision). Stubs would hide real model/API latency and queuing behavior. Rejected lower levels: Integration/System without real model decisions cannot validate true pipeline SLA under actual agentic steps.","test_description":"Execute end-to-end submissions through production-like pipeline invoking real vision and text moderation models, measure submission-to-final-decision latency, and assert p95 <= 5s (and no single request exceeds agreed hard timeout threshold).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.23,"Workflow":0.64}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the AI vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is fallback orchestration on dependency error (unavailable => retry queue). This is testable with module wiring plus controlled dependency failure signal. Rejected higher levels: Agentic disqualified because no model-output-quality assertion; System disqualified because behavior does not require real network/OS effects, only correct handling of an unavailability response.","test_description":"Run service with real queue/repository modules and a classifier adapter stub that returns unavailable/error. Submit image post and assert item enters retry queue with no publish and no auto-approve path taken.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.69,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The moderation decision for a borderline image is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior requires repeated real model-involved decisions over a sequence of submissions and checks cross-attempt consistency (non-determinism/state effects). A single-call agentic test is insufficient because failure appears across sequential decisions/time window. Mocks hide real variance/caching interactions.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image repeatedly (e.g., 20 runs within the defined short window) through the real moderation path; assert decision consistency rate meets policy threshold and no inconsistent publish/hold oscillation violates requirement.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.28,"Workflow":0.62}}]}
